ringing high-order free chunks back into the<br />&gt;system.<br /><br />Correct.  Also, the patch probably doesn't mix all that nicely with the<br />slab allocator which has this nasty habit of wanting larger areas than<br />it really needs (because it can do a better job of cache coloring with a<br />larger area to play with, and it also has a smaller wasted memory<br />impact).  That may undo some of the advantage of the patch - back when I<br />tried it originally the slab code didn't exist. <br /><br />Anyway, I'd like to know what people think about the patch (even just<br />subjective "feels less snappy" or similar)<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
